(20422, 'HIDDEN DRAGON', 'Combining the warp yarn of silk with the weft yarn of cashmere wool, the unique craftsmanship that has gone into the fabric of these garments imbues them with texture and warmth. Each meter of this special cloth requires two days of work on a traditional hand loom by Nepali artisans. This collection is an extreme time-consuming labor of love taking the weaver at least 320 hours to complete and 2-3 kilograms of cashmere. The distinctive SHANG XIA buttons are also carved entirely by hand. Button up collar for a traditional Chinese style or leave it open for a relaxed Western lapel neck. With its subdued soft lines and sense of reserve, the Hidden Dragon embodies the essence of confidence and internalization.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-09 23:40:21', '2014-09-17 20:15:18', NULL, 1, 'product', 8, NULL),
(20426, 'YUN QIU', 'In ancient China, “Yun Qiu” was the softest of furs, and was often used to refer to the emperor who would wear fur when touring his empire. The Yun Qiu collection of gilet jackets are formed from four symmetrical fur panels. The delicate design and tailoring allow these jackets to mold to the body of the wearer whilst remaining generous and comfortable. This collection presents differently in Ovis Aries leather or Orylag, can be worn both sides for matching outfits. The broad arm holes and high back vent give the jacket freedom and mobility. To produce each special gilet, the craftsmen spend over 280 hours in cutting, trimming and sewing. Even in the coldest of weather, simply slip this jacket on as a coat, and you are prepared for anything, poised, elegant and free.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-09 23:40:22', '2014-09-17 20:15:17', NULL, 1, 'product', 9, NULL),
(20427, 'NOBLE', 'The SHANG XIA Nobel collection features highest quality Mongolian cashmere, spun in Nepal and then woven to create the finest fabric. A traditional wooden loom is worked by hand and each warp thread is inserted into the loom, one by one. As it is hand woven, each fabric is unique, integrating natural inclusions. These shawls are not mass-produced, so that no two bolts emerge the same allowing us to create a very special shawl, just for you. The Noble shawls are available in pure cashmere and mixed cashmere and silk with a range of warm colors which makes them perfect for any occasion.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-09 23:40:22', '2014-09-17 20:15:20', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20428, 'WANDERER', 'The yak grows a thick woolen coat to survive the long winters of the Tibetan plains. In the warmth of spring, herders comb out the soft down, grade it, and use it to make the finest clothing. Yak wool is strong and dense and maintains its natural tone even when dyed. The SHANG XIA Wanderer collection is a combination of three tones of hand spun and hand dyed yarn, artfully woven to form this exclusive SHANG XIA fabric. Every Wanderer coat is carefully edged with fine calfskin. It took over 400 hours of painstaking attention to detail. Instead of the multiple panels of modern clothe-making, the Wanderer is based on Chinese traditional dress tailoring, so that the overcoats exude solidity and unity. They are form fitting, but comfortably roomy, like the long cadence of a herding song ringing out across the high plains.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-09 23:40:22', '2014-09-17 20:15:20', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20429, 'CAREFREE', 'Woven from cashmere and cotton, this men’s collection is both soft and comfortable. \n\nWoven from beginning to end in one continuous thread, it is an outstanding technical achievement, evenly finished with no seams. Inspired by Han dynasty costumes, the simple line, color and cross over tie, are the model of confidence and nature of traditional Chinese elegance.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-09 23:40:22', '2014-09-17 20:15:15', NULL, 1, 'product', 10, NULL),
