(20720, 'Wanderer Overcoat', 'Yak grow a thick woolen coat to survive the long winters of the Tibetan plains. In the warmth of spring, herders comb out the soft down, grade it, and use it to make the finest clothing. Yak wool is strong and dense and maintains its natural tone even when dyed. The SHANG XIA Wanderer collection is a combination of three tones of hand spun and hand dyed yarn, artfully woven to form this exclusive SHANG XIA fabric. Every Wanderer coat is carefully edged with fine lambskin. It took over 400 hours of painstaking attention to detail. Instead of the multiple panels of modern clothe-making, the Wanderer is based on Chinese traditional dress tailoring, so that the overcoats exude solidity and unity. They are form fitting, but comfortably roomy, like the long cadence of a herding song ringing out across the high plains.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:05', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20721, 'Wanderer Scarf ', 'Yak grow a thick woolen coat to survive the long winters of the Tibetan plains. In the warmth of spring, herders comb out the soft down, grade it, and use it to make the finest clothing. Yak wool is strong and dense and maintains its natural tone even when dyed. The SHANG XIA Wanderer collection is a combination of three tones of hand spun and hand dyed yarn, artfully woven to form this exclusive SHANG XIA fabric. Every Wanderer coat is carefully edged with fine lambskin. It took over 400 hours of painstaking attention to detail. Instead of the multiple panels of modern clothe-making, the Wanderer is based on Chinese traditional dress tailoring, so that the overcoats exude solidity and unity. They are form fitting, but comfortably roomy, like the long cadence of a herding song ringing out across the high plains.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:05', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20722, 'The Couple', 'Derived from the classic concept of “yin” and “yang” (male and female energy), each pendant is part of a whole embodying polar yet interconnected forces. Carved and polished smooth in 18K gold and 18K platinum respectively, the Couple collection embraces the strength and commitment of life energy forces. ', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:05', '2014-09-18 11:51:52', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20723, 'Garden', 'The SHANG XIA Garden collection includes pendants of Zi­tan, white jade, agate, gold, silver – and, of course, original Taihu Rock, prized over the ages for representing wisdom and immortality. They twist and turn, intriguing and wild, solid and hollow, a surprising form from every side and angle. The Garden collection brings the same sense of contemplative meditation which inspired ancient philosophers and poets, to a single tiny pen­dant to be worn over your heart, inspiring your soul.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:05', '2014-09-18 11:51:52', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20724, 'Bridge', 'Entertaining at home provides a relaxed environment bringing people together around the heart of tea and the home. Whether the tea pot, the tea set or the set of vases are cosseted in bamboo weaving or purely in ceramic, the collection through the shape of its traditional “bridge” handles connects each of us to the warmth of hospitality and friends. The bamboo, is expertly shaved into strands of less than 0.5 mm and woven around the ceramic ware.\n\nThe gong fu tea set, a set of mini tea cups to inhale the fragrance of tea and savor the flavor of tea, is fired in fine porcelain, each piece carefully glazed in translucent white. \n\nThe general tea set and trio of vases, are each expertly finished with hand carved thin bamboo strips woven in mesh. It takes days to completely weave one teapot. The woven bamboo also helps to ensure the tea remains warm.\n', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:06', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20725, 'Ding Tea Set', 'The SHANG XIA Ding tea set draws its inspiration from the traditional three-footed ding. With a teapot, steeping cup and six drinking cups, it brings an element of ritual every time tea is drunk. Every item in the set is fired at over 1300 degrees, giving the porcelain a natural jade-like gloss. The designers dispensed with the two large handles to make this ancient form a little lighter. The result is a modern style that is simple and airy. The full, smooth forms fit the hand however you hold them, making the steeping and drinking of tea a natural, instinctive process: elegant, hospitable and deeply traditional.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:06', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20726, 'Jun Zi Ming Yue Tea Box', 'The bright moon shines between the pines, The clear spring water flows over the stones.\nWang Wei (Tang Dynasty), "Mountain Life on an Autumn Evening"\n\nThe moon is a constant theme in classical Chinese poetry. A dim, restful, expansive vision of moonlight saturates the imagination and the philosophy of many poets. The Yue tea box, part of SHANG XIA''s Junzi collection, was inspired by classical carry cases, with their fine, self-contained designs. Like the bright, clear moon, they represent beauty and peace. The box is in three layers, each layer perfectly structured and functional. The box''s contents can be stored safely and logically, so that they are easy to find, simple to stow and light to carry. The bottom layer holds the teapot in a shaped cushion. The middle layer is divided into four quarters two snugly hold four teacups, and has a shaped rim which allows the tea tray to fit perfectly on top within the lid. The handle is carved from a single piece of walnut with an attractive arch. While carrying the box, it locks the layers securely in place. A dragon-scale pattern is carved on the surface of the tea tray, and it has a space inside it, allowing it to serve the functions of both the traditional tea tray and the water reservoir. The tray is made of Corian, a light and durable material, in the color of tea. \n', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:06', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20727, 'Le Chant du Thé Arhat Tea Cups', 'The luminous porcelain of the “arhat” tea cups is decorated with motifs of longevity peaches, Lingzhi clouds and leaves of the Bodhi tree, each image painted by hand by an artist with over ten years of experience.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:06', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20728, 'Jun Zi Mahjong', 'Mahjong is a traditional Chinese game. The SHANG XIA Jun Zi collection is inspired by traditional Chinese carry boxes. Nestled on five levels, the Jun Zi mahjong case contains 4 boxes of mahjong tiles and racks, a box of chips, chip holder and dice. With your choice of tiles in precious Indian sandalwood and Zitan, marked with geometric abstraction pattern, your every game will be infused with a gentle, natural, elegant aroma. Time and space seem to be manipulated at the fingertips of the players. Over 2,000 hours of craft have gone into making each mahjong set.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:06', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20729, 'Sound of Tea ', 'SHANG XIA Le chant du Thé crockery brings warm colors to a modern evolution of tableware, filled with flavor and companionship. It offers a generous provision of plates, serving dishes and bowls. The whole set lends refinement and class to the dining table. The unique designs on the plates are taken from paintings inspired by the Confucian Temple, the Temple of Heaven and the bamboo slips. They bring the wisdom of ancient architecture and handicrafts into the ceramic, and the bold colors remind us of the great sweep of China''s culinary tradition. Let a simple meal take on centuries of flavor and meaning.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:07', '2014-09-18 11:51:50', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20730, 'Twilight ', 'The Twlight series is a set of wooden cases in rich Zitan wood, inlaid with delicate carved bamboo. They may be used on a dresser, for jewellery, for cosmetics, for perfume, or as a pen case in the study. Skillfully interwoven the traditional sayagata pattern with the SHANGXIA logo creates a unique carved bamboo motif for the Twlight series. The bamboo carvers bring concentration and years of honed technique to their work. Using tools they make themselves, they split the bamboo into 0.5mm-thin strips, then cut 0.5mm-wide notches, and divide the strips into 5mm sections. Then, patiently and precisely, they piece together these sections, no larger than a grain of rice, into a composite image. A 10 square centimeters carving contains over 1,000 tiny sections, placed with such accuracy that the individual pieces become invisible and melt into an organic whole. As with traditional window screens, the design creates an airy and satisfying interplay of light and shade. Meanwhile, the form of these irregularly sized cases imitates the graceful lines of Ming Dynasty furniture; seen under the crystal Twlight, a classical past seems to emerge once again. The poet Su Shi once wrote, "Dancing in the half-light, you are far from this world." Twlight exists in a space outside time.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:07', '2014-09-18 11:51:50', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20731, 'Wu Fu ', 'The SHANG XIA Wufu series draws on the Qing Dynasty flared vase form, but allows the vase to sleekly separate into a set of plates and containers. We blended two traditions, using lacquer to recreate the beauty of porcelain. This series uses a palette of five colors to echo the “Wufu”, each associated with one of the great porcelain kilns: Ru, Guan, Ge, Ding and Jun. The crackled porcelain effect on the outside of the vase was recreated using a painstaking technique of eggshell and lacquer. The eggshell is carefully cracked and pieced precisely back together. The pieces must be of uniform size, and must fit seamlessly together. Only the steadiest and most experienced lacquerworkers can do this delicate work. The gilded interior involves a slow finishing process, then the minute work of piecing gilt onto surface. It takes calmness and dedication to align the pieces seamlessly together. The color is infused into the lacquer, so the process of repeated polishing and burnishing brings it out in a warm gloss, understated and classic. The “Wufu” are: long life, prosperity, health, virtue and a peaceful passing. They represent a long life, well lived.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:07', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20732, 'DA TIAN DI - ARMCHAIR (ZITAN)', 'Tian Di encompasses the heavens and the earth. This collection of furniture is made up of clean lines and soft arcs, generous and open in spirit, ready to contain the heavens and the earth. The Da Tian Di armchair is a light evolution of the traditional Ming "official''s hat chair". It reverses the traditional Ming furniture concept of a rounded exterior and square centre and presents a square exterior and round interior. The result is a more modern line, revealing the deep craft that goes into its construction. SHANG XIA has ingeniously combined the simplicity and elegance of Ming furniture with the Western lounge concept, giving this new official''s hat chair a soft seat and back, making it a more user-friendly experience. The Zitan is paired with high quality braided leather cushions. Tanners expertly slice whole cowhides into long strips, just 3.8mm wide. They are woven in a style similar to k''o-ssu silk tapestry, strip over strip, each piece entirely handmade, for a textured, living, breathing finish. The construction of each chair takes six to nine months with each step in the process being performed with needlepoint precision. The result is a finely crafted modern heirloom with a timeless appeal.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:07', '2014-09-18 11:51:51', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20733, 'DA TIAN DI - TEA TABLE (ZITAN)', 'The SHANG XIA Da Tian Di collection is a reinvention of tea furniture, combining the tea tray and table in a single item. Made from Zitan wood, in a spare and classic form, providing elegance and utility. Reversing the traditional Ming furniture concept, of a rounded exterior and square center, the Da Tian Di collection presents a square exterior and round interior in a modern take on a classic aesthetic. Opening the table top reveals the tray and electric kettle. The process of construction requires at least 2,000 labor hours for each item, including hand crafted joints and polishing to provide a sliken glossy luster. The tray itself is make of Duan inkstone, one of the four most precious types of inkstone prized since antiquity and increasingly harder to find. The custom-made Da Tian Di collection of tea furniture casts a mantle of meditation across the reception space. It is for those who understand tea, who take the time to sit and savor their tea, and who receive guests with their finest tea.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:08', '2014-09-18 11:51:50', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20734, 'Junzi Screen ', 'The SHANG XIA Junzi screen is a traditionally-constructed four-panel foldable screen. It consists of wooden frames and embroidered scrolls, which can be rolled up or left down as needed, just like a painting. The scrolls, designed exclusively for this item, are in subdued tones with a sense of density, easily matching any household decoration. The mobility and ease of adjustment mean that the screen can be used in any season; in winter, particularly, it can shape a warm oasis. The frame is designed on the principle of square exterior and rounded interior, with a coherent, simple form. The panels can be turned to any angle as required, and will remain stable whatever the formation. They can also be folded away for ease of storage. The four panels each have a unique width and shape; together they possess a harmony and rhythm. Simple elements, combined with grace like blocks of color in an abstract painting.', NULL, 'en', '2014-09-18 11:49:08', '2014-09-18 11:51:50', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20735, '吟游', '「上下」的农民画丝巾系列是一组充满幽默感的作品系列。发源自上海郊县的当代民间绘画——金山农民画，笔触质朴简洁，色彩鲜艳悦目，充满现代感和来自民间的生命力。「上下」与金山农民画艺术家合作，以充满想象力的方式演绎多种传统题材画作，并以「上下」特别定制的真丝和羊绒面料，精心印制成多彩丝巾系列。\n“吟游”系列以清代画家王翚的作品《康熙出行图》为灵感，为庆祝「上下」虹桥机场店开幕而特别创作。丝巾以优质羊绒和真丝经纬相织而成，纹理清晰，触感轻柔，色彩饱满而生动。希望能为旅途增加一丝悦动色彩，也为城市生活带来一份旅行的心情。\n', NULL, 'cn', '2014-09-18 11:49:16', '2014-09-18 11:53:31', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20736, '乐', '「上下」的“乐”系列采用最高品质的蒙古羊绒制作。看似旗袍和对襟衫，其实滚边、立领、对襟、斜襟和盘扣，都是由高级机织技术编织而成的图案。单色系列由独特的“米粒”针法织成，而盘扣则是由钩针手工钩出的立体装饰。“乐”的设计是一种游戏和玩笑的心态，也隐喻中国传统的道家哲学，真真假假，皆为虚幻，唯一重要的是个人的体悟。这个系列的女装有旗袍的优雅和中国情调，又有羊绒织物的蓬松柔软，穿着简单方便，是冬天里温暖的陪伴。', NULL, 'cn', '2014-09-18 11:49:18', '2014-09-18 11:53:30', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20737, '乐', '「上下」的“乐”系列采用最高品质的蒙古羊绒制作。看似旗袍和对襟衫，其实滚边、立领、对襟、斜襟和盘扣，都是由高级机织技术编织而成的图案。单色系列由独特的“米粒”针法织成，而盘扣则是由钩针手工钩出的立体装饰。“乐”的设计是一种游戏和玩笑的心态，也隐喻中国传统的道家哲学，真真假假，皆为虚幻，唯一重要的是个人的体悟。这个系列的女装有旗袍的优雅和中国情调，又有羊绒织物的蓬松柔软，穿着简单方便，是冬天里温暖的陪伴。', NULL, 'cn', '2014-09-18 11:49:18', '2014-09-18 11:53:30', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20738, '乐', '「上下」的“乐”系列采用最高品质的蒙古羊绒制作。看似旗袍和对襟衫，其实滚边、立领、对襟、斜襟和盘扣，都是由高级机织技术编织而成的图案。单色系列由独特的“米粒”针法织成，而盘扣则是由钩针手工钩出的立体装饰。“乐”的设计是一种游戏和玩笑的心态，也隐喻中国传统的道家哲学，真真假假，皆为虚幻，唯一重要的是个人的体悟。这个系列的女装有旗袍的优雅和中国情调，又有羊绒织物的蓬松柔软，穿着简单方便，是冬天里温暖的陪伴。', NULL, 'cn', '2014-09-18 11:49:18', '2014-09-18 11:53:30', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20739, '揽月', '“俱怀逸兴壮思飞，欲上青天揽明月。”\n——唐·李白\n \n \n「上下」以日常而精巧的中国竹篮为灵感，以立体皮具制作工艺，模拟竹篮的肌理与构造，创作了“揽月”系列立体编织皮质包袋。创造性的细节设计，超越了以往皮具制作的经验，“揽月”系列让两种不同的工艺在同一时空碰撞、对话、交融，给工艺制作带来了新的挑战，也带来了全新的效果呈现。\n', NULL, 'cn', '2014-09-18 11:49:18', '2014-09-18 11:53:30', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL),
(20740, '日月', '“日月”系列选择细密柔软的上等双面羊绒，复杂的手工收边，恰到好处地形成了舒朗的廓形线条，犹如逸笔草草，自然勾勒与提炼出衣料的风神骨相。在中国哲学观念中，日、月分别代表了阳与阴，《周易》中谓：“日月丽乎天”，即是言明“日月”乃宇宙之道，双生变幻，蕴意无穷。这个系列能够随心而定、双面穿着，应对不同场合的需求。男装灵感自传统对襟服饰，设计为大衣与西装两类，都拥有静谧、沉定的配色，恰如静水流深，初衷不改。女款则延续曲裾深衣的经典式样，打破了传统肩线设计的局限，有连袖成片的大衣与马甲两类可选，配色上表达出煦暖喜意的气象，一如天光烂漫，典婉动人。身着“日月”，仿佛游于广袤无垠的天地之间，从容往来，自在而寻有无之境。', NULL, 'cn', '2014-09-18 11:49:19', '2014-09-18 11:53:30', NULL, 1, 'product', 0, NULL);
